{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","required_reality_check_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS/LLM-DEP: correctness depends on the vision model actually judging explicitness; a stubbed classifier would hide misclassification failures. A higher Workflow level was considered and rejected because this behavior hinges on one model judgment plus a deterministic hold/publish action, not multiple model-dependent decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Run the moderation flow with real explicit-image samples against the real vision model and verify each submission is marked held-for-review and is absent from the published feed/read API.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.14,"Agentic":0.74,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","required_reality_check_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: this is model robustness/quality (detecting obfuscated hate speech). Deterministic mocks cannot validate the model’s real semantic judgment. Workflow was rejected because the behavior is a single text-classification decision, not a multi-step agent pipeline.","test_description":"Use a corpus of obfuscated hate-speech texts and submit them through the real text moderation model path; assert they are consistently flagged and routed to human review.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.84,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: this is primarily orchestration/state handoff (both checks pass -> publish path). Rejection gate for higher levels: behavior text says 'passes both content checks', so it does not require proving model output quality, only correct downstream routing and persistence. No explicit real-OS/network/subprocess contract is required by the behavior text.","test_description":"Wire moderation service + repositories/queues in-process, stub both classifiers to return 'safe', submit a post, then assert publish state is persisted and no hold/drop state is recorded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","required_reality_check_level":"Workflow","justification":"MULTI-STEP + LLM-DEP: this explicitly spans multiple agentic steps in sequence (vision check then text check) and asserts an end-to-end SLA across the chained pipeline. Lower System/Agentic-only checks were rejected because they do not validate the full multi-step model-dependent path under one submission lifecycle.","test_description":"Execute end-to-end submissions that invoke real image and text models in sequence, measure submission-to-final-decision latency, and assert p95 (or specified percentile) stays <=5s under peak-hour representative load.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.25,"Workflow":0.55}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the AI vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","required_reality_check_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA/SYSTEM TRIAD error-path: this behavior targets external dependency unavailability handling and requires validating real error-path contract (timeouts/5xx/connection failure) and externally visible queue side effect. Agentic was rejected because no correctness claim depends on model judgment quality; only outage handling behavior matters.","test_description":"Trigger real vision-service unavailability (or a real network fault/5xx in a test environment), submit image posts, verify they are placed in retry queue and not auto-approved/published, and confirm via queue readback/status API.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.74,"Agentic":0.14,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The moderation decision for a borderline image is consistent when the same image is submitted multiple times within a short window.","required_reality_check_level":"Workflow","justification":"LLM-DEP + MULTI-STEP cross-step state anchor: pass/fail depends on consistency across repeated real model decisions over a sequence of submissions. A single-call Agentic test is insufficient because it cannot detect drift/inconsistency across runs within the window.","test_description":"Submit the same borderline image repeatedly within the target short window through the real moderation pipeline, capture each decision, and assert consistency criteria (e.g., all held or all published, or bounded variance threshold) across the sequence.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.01,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.31,"Workflow":0.63}}]}
